Subject: Re: [T2] Tire size

> Is that data correct? Just curious about what seems, at first glance, to not
> make sense.
>
> Bridgestone: 195 diameter is .1" smaller than the 185, and is +14 revs/mile.
>
> Yoko: 195 diameter is .1" larger, and is only 1 rev/mile different.
>
> The Yoko 195 is LARGER? And while a .1" change produces 14 rev/mile
> difference in the Bridgestone, it only yields 1 rev/mile diffrence in the
> Yoko?

Yes it is correct.
Because every tire is made differently.
A tire is a circle until you put a car on it and then it is a flat circle
and every circle flattens a little differently.
So they measure it and politely supply the data.

